This output confirms your disconnected catalog is actually healthy for SR-IOV Network Operator.

You DO have:

latest 4.16 bundles

proper channel (stable)

entries available

currentCSV present


So the issue is NOT missing package manifest.


---

Now the important part:

Your installed subscription earlier showed:

CHANNEL = stable

But your installed CSVs were old:

4.14 / 4.15

While package manifest now offers:

sriov-network-operator.v4.16.0-202510211319

That means OLM sees upgrade path.


---

Most likely causes now:

1. InstallPlan not generated

Check:

oc get installplan -A | grep sriov

If no new 4.16 installplan: → Subscription resolution stuck.


---

2. Subscription stuck

Run:

oc describe sub sriov-network-operator -n openshift-sriov-network-operator

Look especially for:

ConstraintsNotSatisfiable

ResolutionFailed

Bundle unpack failed

no operators found



---

3. Old CSV blocking replacement chain

Very common in disconnected clusters.

Check:

oc get csv -n openshift-sriov-network-operator

If you see:

multiple CSVs

one Replacing

one Pending

one Deleting


then chain is stuck.


---

4. Catalog pod restarted recently

Your catalog pod age was only ~45m.

Sometimes OLM cache becomes inconsistent.


---

Recommended fix now

Step 1 — Backup subscription YAML

oc get sub sriov-network-operator -n openshift-sriov-network-operator -o yaml > sriov-sub.yaml


---

Step 2 — Delete failed/pending installplans

oc delete installplan <name> -n openshift-sriov-network-operator

Safe.


---

Step 3 — Check CSV chain

oc get csv -n openshift-sriov-network-operator

If old failed CSVs exist:

oc delete csv <failed-csv> -n openshift-sriov-network-operator

DO NOT delete current succeeded CSV unless necessary.


---

Step 4 — Restart catalog-operator

Sometimes needed in disconnected env:

oc delete pod -n openshift-operator-lifecycle-manager -l app=catalog-operator


---

Step 5 — If still stuck → recreate subscription

oc delete sub sriov-network-operator -n openshift-sriov-network-operator

Then reapply:

oc apply -f sriov-sub.yaml

OLM should generate fresh installplan.


---

Very important

SR-IOV and PTP operators are tightly coupled with:

node drains

MCP updates

NTO

performance add-on

kernel modules


Sometimes upgrade waits because daemonsets are unhealthy.

Check:

oc get co

and:

oc get mcp

and:

oc get pods -n openshift-sriov-network-operator

If MCP degraded/updating forever: operator upgrade may intentionally pause.
